      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Research suggests that small businesses in low-cost-of-living areas like yours are often not as vulnerable to the immediate effects of minimum wage hikes, as they have already built-in cost savings from lower operating expenses. However, some studies have shown that small businesses in these areas may still be forced to pass on increased labor costs to customers in the form of higher prices, which can have a disproportionate impact on low-income residents who visit your cafe regularly. These businesses may also be forced to reduce hours or staff part-time employees to maintain profitability.",
